  </section>
  <section>
   <title>Moving around the screen elements by using the keyboard </title>
   <p>To move around the elements on the <ph conref="../TextEntities.dita#TextEntities/ISMgui"/>,
            press Tab.</p>
   <p>When a menu tab has focus, a box is displayed around the text for that menu tab. You can then
    move between the menus <uicontrol>Home</uicontrol>,  <uicontrol>Messaging</uicontrol>,
     <uicontrol>Monitoring</uicontrol>,  <uicontrol>Server</uicontrol>,
     <uicontrol>Cluster</uicontrol> and  <uicontrol>Web UI</uicontrol>, by using the arrow keys. To
    go to the options that are available from the menu that is in focus, press Shift+F10. Use the
    space bar to select an item from the list.</p>
   <p>To access check boxes located within a grid, press Tab to move focus to the grid. Then, use
    the arrow keys to move to the check box you want to select. Press F2 to focus on the check box,
    and press Spacebar to select or clear the check box. To move focus away from the check box,
    press Tab. </p>
